    "Another possibility, proposed by Lieu et al. (2022) is that GWs can lose energy while propagating through the intergalactic medium via the acceleration of charged particles.",
    "Owing to the much higher thermal velocity of electrons over protons and the presence of an intergalactic medium magnetic field, a significant fraction of the GWs can be converted to EM radiation.",
    "The ensuing electromagnetic intensity is inversely proportional to frequency.",
    "Partial GW loss via this mechanism could explain a flatter-than-expected GWB spectrum.",
    "The efficiency of such a mechanism depends on the strength of the intergalactic medium magnetic field."
  ],
